The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Chambers hail stress on development

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, March 21: The industry feels that finance minister Asim Dasgupta has put the right thrust on small-scale industries (SSI), agriculture and infrastructure development. However, they do not favour the implementation of VAT in the state.

 MCC president Aditya V. Agarwal said, ?We welcome the plan outlay on industry and power generation as well as the proposal to double the credit availability for the SSI sector and exemption of education and employment cess for the tea industry.?

 On VAT, Bharat Chamber of Commerce vice-president P. R. Agarwal said, ?If other states are reluctant to implement VAT simultaneously, the trade and industry in Bengal will be at a disadvantage.? BNCCI president S. N. Nundy said Dasgupta has placed a growth-oriented budget. 




